sql:
SELECT AVG(od600nm) AS average_od600nm, MIN(od600nm) AS minimum_od600nm, MAX(od600nm) AS maximum_od600nm
FROM od600nm_readings
WHERE experiment_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'YourSpecificStrainName' is the actual name of the strain used in the experiment; 
- 'YourSpecificTimepoint' is the actual timepoint when the reading was taken; 
- 'YourSpecificLabName' is the actual name of the lab where the experiment is conducted; 
- 'high' growth rate is a specific value for the result of the experiment.
